commit_message:
CI: fix kayobe-tox-molecule job

The kayobe-tox-molecule job is currently failing on stable/train and
earlier branches. This was caused by the 13.0 release of the 'sh'
package [1]. A 13.1 release fixed this for Python 3, but there is no fix
available for Python 2 currently.

This change works around the issue by pinning 'sh' to <13.0 in
test-requirements.txt.

[1] https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/issues/2676

Change-Id: I0df1dadb3b48736cdbd25112517e524533550210
(cherry picked from commit 5f836518cfe964d2733f5a7db327fbfad3b8e8b0)

running Stein jobs on xenial.

commit_message:
[Community goal] Update contributor documentation

As the Ussuri goal we have an OpenStack project wide contributing
documentation template [1]. pyhton-novaclient use its own bug or feature
tracking LP and core team is also not exactly same as nova  so adding
its own contributor guide with keeping common links from nova
with python-novaclient specific information.

Also the top level CONTRIBUTING.rst template has been changed in the
cookiecutter repo[2]. So this patch updates the CONTRIBUTING.rst according
to the new template.

[1] https://opendev.org/openstack/cookiecutter/src/branch/master/%7b%7bcookiecutter.repo_name%7d%7d/doc/source/contributor/contributing.rst
[2] https://review.opendev.org/#/c/696001

Change-Id: Ie255a2f3e358323da1132d3c7354651ea7719ae0
Story: #2007236
Task: #38567

commit_message:
Remove deprecated secret decrypt

This patch removes the deprecated secret decription from
the /v1/secrets/{secret-id} route when using Accept headers
that are not 'application/json'.

The only way to decrypt after this patch is merged will be
using the /v1/secrets/{secret-id}/payload route.

Change-Id: I1ae1b333ad078ebf0e0a99c75f89b78e8c9d32a3

Drop bumps for stable/rocky

patches if any will occur.

commit_message:
Update TOX_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/ussuri

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

Until the requirements repository has as stable/ussuri branch, tests will
continue to use the upper-constraints list on master.

Change-Id: I98d37f68b6b2deca95e09ef8c2a4e23f32838e60

commit_message:
Add ironic-python-agent-builder to grenade projects and use netboot

It appears that grenade now requires ironic-python-agent-builder
to be in the projects list in order for clone operations to take
place.

Also switch to netboot as the default boot option is local now.

Change-Id: Ibf66351137d9f4221c9c191b4d9a4b2272f0f516

commit_message:
Fix ironic inspector rule creation idempotency

Ironic inspector rules are registered both with the seed and (if using)
overcloud ironic inspector services. These tasks often show up as
changed even when no configuration changes have been made that would
affect the rules.

This is caused by inspector returning default values for fields that may
be omitted in the requested rule. This change fixes the issue by
including those defaults in the comparison.

Change-Id: Ia24e328d4531201d76a65b6385e4463bb1f3c5c6
Story: 2007399
Task: 38997

commit_message:
Revert "Add stunnel container for Glance service"

This reverts commit 935adb59131caf66455a7d59c2af7cc42186e282.

It seems we cannot use stunnel on Ubuntu because
of no support for current OpenSSL. See [1].

We have some alternatives to replace stunnel:
- HAProxy (image ready; in progress)
- Apache2 (only embedded, no image)
- Nginx (possibly in the future)

[1] https://review.opendev.org/707131

Change-Id: If1140b293423ad3173cb3a4e1f19abbfecdaf2f6

commit_message:
Use default release-selector

Ensure that the charm uses the default charms.openstack release
selector - as this is a subordinate charm this results in the
'openstack-dashboard' package being used for OpenStack release
determination.

Drop package_codenames and release_pkg from class definitions
as these are not needed.

Change-Id: I678bf71aaa8c57fb15cc394daaa7761acd44cbf1

commit_message:
Use default release selector

Ensure that the charm uses the default release selector from
charms.openstack.  This will ensure that the charm correctly
detects the OpenStack release and switches between Python 2
and Python 3 TrilioVault packages correctly.

Change-Id: I472f792a982861c321cb32a0177a5f07df87cbda

commit_message:
Add support for encrypting heat api

This patch introduces an optional backend encryption for Heat
service. When used in conjunction with enabling TLS for service API
endpoints, network communcation will be encrypted end to end, from
client through HAProxy to the Heat service.

Change-Id: Ic12f7574135dcaed2a462e902c775a55176ff03b
Partially-Implements: blueprint add-ssl-internal-network
Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/722028/

commit_message:
Modify Heat container to execute httpd setup

This patch modifies the Dockerfile for the Heat container so
that the root user will execute the container setup scripts. This
enables the container httpd configuration script to execute.

Partially-Implements: blueprint add-ssl-internal-network
Change-Id: Ib7936161bb42ee36d7875baffa31af5dff409844

commit_message:
Update TOX_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/ussuri

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

Until the requirements repository has as stable/ussuri branch, tests will
continue to use the upper-constraints list on master.

Change-Id: I7d153a8fc5825059e7ad452761e3f30d01d4d65c

commit_message:
Make sure octavia uses internal endpoint to barbican

The octavia service communicates to the barbican service with
public endpoint_type by default[1], it should use internal
like other services.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/octavia/blob/0056b5175f89070164849501ec6d960549b95e34/octavia/common/config.py#L533-L537

Closes-Bug: #1875618
Change-Id: I90d2b0aeac090a3e2366341e260232fc1f0d6492
(cherry picked from commit 01ae01ec26769d15059a45432c8accffc10f0da1)

commit_message:
Update TOX_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/ussuri

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

Until the requirements repository has as stable/ussuri branch, tests will
continue to use the upper-constraints list on master.

Change-Id: I94e34ecb7a1c9fef5b793bfe776af3b44a5c06c8

commit_message:
Update hacking version to 1.1.x

This commit updates hacking version in test-requirements
and fixes some related pep8 issues

Also ignores false positive bandit test
B105: hardcoded_password_string,
B106: hardcoded_password_funcarg
based on variable or argument names.
For more info refer [1][2]

[1] https://bandit.readthedocs.io/en/latest/plugins/b105_hardcoded_password_string.html
[2] https://bandit.readthedocs.io/en/latest/plugins/b106_hardcoded_password_funcarg.html

Change-Id: If779ebad11926594961577e0744093a8ba691610
Story: 2004930

commit_message:
Add appendix for TrilioVault deployment

Add new appendix to cover deployment and configuration
of TrilioVault.

TrilioVault is a commericial, propriety product and is
not part of OpenStack, but is deployable using free and open
source charms which form part of the OpenStack Charms
project.

Change-Id: Ifdaf0ec7eec1ce790b79a17952621eeb8dc65d61

commit_message:
Move tempest-full-rocky-py3 job defintion to stackviz

tempest-full-rocky-py3 was defined in Tempest which is going
to removed[1] from there as rocky is in Extended Maintainance state.

Stackviz need to run the rocky job as it support py3.5 env also.

Renaming the job to avoid the zuul error of duplciate definition of same
job name.

[1] https://review.opendev.org/#/c/722183/1
Change-Id: Ieb1ce1f5c712ffedbacab8dd58cf75cc138deca4

commit_message:
Fix multiple issues

Multiple issues combined to pass CI

1. drop tripleo-common-tempest-plugin

This is not needed plugin without any branches or releases. And wants Python 3
while we have Py2 for CentOS 7.

Original Change-Id: I9cab91b82941ea125b16d19e68722ce41a1f11f2
14:41 < hrw> is  tripleo-common-tempest-plugin your stuff?
14:43 <@EmilienM> yes and it does nothing. I thought we removed that?
14:43 <@EmilienM> apparently it's still here https://github.com/openstack/tripleo-common-tempest-plugin
14:43 <@EmilienM> we should burn it, weshay|ruck ^
14:44 < hrw> EmilienM: also fine to drop from train?
14:44 <@EmilienM> burn it everywhere you can
14:44 < hrw> THANKS
14:44 <@EmilienM> it has never been useful
14:44 <@EmilienM> and people who started it left
14:48 <@weshay|ruck> EmilienM, yup

2. Sensu: Remove ceph and process-checks plugins from client

The sensu image became unbuildable, failing to install the ceph plugin:

    Unable to resolve dependencies: sensu-plugins-ceph requires english (= 0.6.3)

This has happened because the author of the 'english' gem has seen fit
to publish a new 0.7.0 release, and 'yank' [1] all previous releases
from rubygems.

This change removes the ceph and process-checks plugins, which both
suffer from a dependency on the yanked english 0.6.3.

[1] https://rubygems.org/gems/english/versions/0.6.3

Original Change-Id: I9d34413fa10b5a2920aca60b08141bfaddcc7415
Closes-Bug: #1871600
(cherry picked from commit 818dc4d6ff12a3119be072e0c68e2d2c8da9b799)
(cherry picked from commit 2d1017be3fd658011fc5a86bd38b7265da306ea3)

3. Use freezer queens releases

There are no freezer releases in Rocky, so these packages stayed on
master. This is now python 3 only, so fails to build. Pin to Queens
6.0.0 releases.

4. Pin elasticsearch gem to <7.6.0 in fluentd

Since the release of the elasticsearch 7.6.0 gem, the fluentd image
fails to build on Ubuntu due to a transitive dependency on faraday.

ERROR:  Error installing fluent-plugin-elasticsearch:
    faraday requires Ruby version >= 2.3.

Pin elasticsearch to <7.6.0.

Change-Id: I6200ed527244313107666753257f52d4b9305dd3

commit_message:
Add Github mirroring job to all official repos

Now that the Github repositories have been cleaned up of refs/changes
entries, we can enable per-repo mirroring globally.

Note that:
- openstack/release-test was already added as a test
- for repos that did not have an entry in projects.yaml, we create one

Needed-By: https://review.opendev.org/718478
Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/724329
Change-Id: Ia72b3271a65d38ea6b5e4ad03af5813193c47926

commit_message:
Fix broken unit tests because of list in notification drivers

Because the value for oslo_messaging_notifications/driver is now
a list[1], we should expect that a list is set when multiple drivers
are given.

commit_message:
Add official-openstack-repo-jobs project template

Add a project template for jobs attached to official and active
OpenStack repositories (like the GitHub mirroring).

Change-Id: I1004508c66d53a5e3c11af1e3dbf411338cfd25f

commit_message:
Hacking: enforce usage of autospec=True in tests

Using autospec ensures that mocked functions are called with correct
arguments, so it's highly desired to have it.

Change-Id: I9c8395adf852495d2ef6db732d727990e8abd5d7

commit_message:
Rebuild reactive APIs for layer-basic regression

Fix regression in layer-basic which failed to unpack new dependencies
properly during the upgrade-charm hook.

Github Issue: #166
Closes Bug: #1875496

Change-Id: I680f276e255ddf667ccc228acbd88576661c6d26

(5 comments)'}, {'account_id': 4690, 'date': '2020-04-29 15:26:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 22: Code-Review-1

I really don't think we should consider merging this unless the issues in the patch above are resolved. The TL;DR on the discussion is that this patch series is aiming to clean up instances that are "not tracked" in the database because a database archive ran during a period when nova-compute was "down". And so the reap period task cannot clean them up. This part of the issue has been resolved by adding the --before option to the 'nova-manage db archive_deleted_rows' command.

So, this series should not be targeting that scenario, but in its current state, it still is.

The other way that instances can become "orphaned" is via bugs/failures in the middle of migrations. To this, we would prefer an approach where we fix the bugs and gaps in rollback related to migrations instead of adding a periodic task that tries to detect which guests are safe to kill depending on their task state, etc. This is not straightforward because you don't want to kill a guest that is in the middle of migrating and temporarily can't be "seen" because its instance.host hasn't been flipped to the destination yet. I really think that we should just fix/harden migration problems instead of trying to add a periodic task like this one.'}]

commit_message:
Clean up orphan instances virt driver

The VM is not tracked by database could still query from libvirt
by UUID, then deleted or power off by UUID. This commit introduce
libvirt driver for periodicly clean the orphan instances.

Partial-Bug: #1820802

commit_message:
[NetApp] Fix share replica failing for 'transfer in progress' error

This patch fix an issue in NetApp driver share replica periodic
check that erroneuouly set a share replica to error after receiving
a 'Another transfer is in progress' error. The driver now skips the
resync operation for all expected transfer in progress relationship
status.

Closes-Bug: #1848889
Change-Id: If82aaa184db84660389f82654279f3c5b238fd51
(cherry picked from commit 572be43bb03a67376b52a11c70e587eb160b68a3)
(cherry picked from commit cc2dea14a514ad1a7025d904074307817c60e3ce)

[{'created': '2020-04-11 02:22:00.000000000', 'message': "[NetApp] Fix driver to honor standard extra specs

During migration and manage/unmanage operations, if we used standard
extra_specs format (e.g. 'thin_provisioning'='True') instead of
NetApp based extra_specs format (e.g. 'netapp:thin_provisioned'='True'),
NetApp driver used to ignore these standard extra_specs settings
and continued the operation with the default option.
The driver is now fixed to handle this issue by honouring the
standard extra_specs during migration and manage/unmanage.

Change-Id: I48f4d966201fc8d6bd6eec0c37f1575b434310e7
Closes-Bug: #1707084
(cherry picked from commit 9250e02b56fa4a0d93fe4c32cdfac4eceab8d095)
(cherry picked from commit 678ea79f85e53ec21a0fb74758875b3a7ebe1aa7)
"}]
commit_message:
[NetApp] Fix driver to honor standard extra specs

During migration and manage/unmanage operations, if we used standard
extra_specs format (e.g. 'thin_provisioning'='True') instead of
NetApp based extra_specs format (e.g. 'netapp:thin_provisioned'='True'),
NetApp driver used to ignore these standard extra_specs settings
and continued the operation with the default option.
The driver is now fixed to handle this issue by honouring the
standard extra_specs during migration and manage/unmanage.

Change-Id: I48f4d966201fc8d6bd6eec0c37f1575b434310e7
Closes-Bug: #1707084
(cherry picked from commit 9250e02b56fa4a0d93fe4c32cdfac4eceab8d095)
(cherry picked from commit 678ea79f85e53ec21a0fb74758875b3a7ebe1aa7)

commit_message:
Update TOX_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/ussuri

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

Until the requirements repository has as stable/ussuri branch, tests will
continue to use the upper-constraints list on master.

Change-Id: Icdde4120bc502c27391831321a96e01b9818aa95

commit_message:
[NetApp] Fix share shrink error status

This patch fixes the error raised by NetApp driver when the user try
to shrink a share to a size smaller than the current used space. Now
the driver raises "shrinking_possible_data_loss" instead of
"shrinking_error".

Change-Id: I01a549a0e299ae0d0d9b603a9d0797f16f4b68b3
Closes-Bug: #1858328
(cherry picked from commit c169902d41ef2b70ce1c1181408bc0916a7ea319)
(cherry picked from commit 97a913209825f975ccfc2d76c91f4215d02622ad)

commit_message:
Fix tenant_id for a new port.

To successfully create a port in a shared network which belongs
to a different tenant, the tenant of the new port should be same
as the tenant of a request user.

Closes-bug: #1815461
Change-Id: Ia243f213b23f3f34845de5d97e8eaa5aa6979e76

commit_message:
fix bug in quota checking

When project quota set unlimited(-1), and user in the
project is limited to a value.Then project quota must
smaller than project usage when checking quotas, which
means the value 'overs' is not None.
In this case, even though the user not over the quota,
but they can not create share

Closes-bug: #1872872

Change-Id: Id9e2bcb5d30d2b81b0723dd296b537ac7d4519f2
(cherry picked from commit 780053968270900a1402fa0db4ae96bd16060ad4)
(cherry picked from commit 73837ce05a9bf07c7dd4e15c98eee511ff9e1a10)
(cherry picked from commit f2afb50fbbd6ec1b14ba93a64d292cbc66e53cfe)

commit_message:
tox: Keeping going with docs

1. Sphinx 1.8 introduced [1] the '--keep-going' argument which, as its name
suggests, keeps the build running when it encounters non-fatal errors.
This is exceptionally useful in avoiding a continuous edit-build loop
when undertaking large doc reworks where multiple errors may be
introduced.

2. Remove the py27 from tox since magnum already drop support python 2.7

[1] https://github.com/sphinx-doc/sphinx/commit/e3483e9b045

Change-Id: I6e713b51cf9fac87e696fdfce8156f656a0f1df5

commit_message:
Update TOX_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/ussuri

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

Until the requirements repository has as stable/ussuri branch, tests will
continue to use the upper-constraints list on master.

Change-Id: I637808fa6e19232a4702a486794db549340bf558

Adapt to Octavia Certificate Configuration Guide.

This patch updates the octavia controller deployment to use the
latest octavia certificate configuration guide [1]. The dual CA changes
were introduced in Train.

[1] https://docs.openstack.org/octavia/latest/admin/guides/certificates.html

Closes-Bug: #1862133

commit_message:
Bump default tox env from py37 to py38

Python 3.8 is now our highest level supported python runtime.
This updates the default tox target environments to swap out
py37 for py38 to make sure local development testing is
covering this version.

This does not impact zuul jobs in any way, nor prevent local
tests against py37. It just changes the default if none is
explicitly provided.

Change-Id: I1992bad2ee6bffade2f937cc0d8dc6ae800f4159
Signed-off-by: Sean McGinnis <sean.mcginnis@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Improve VLAN allocations synchronization

In order to reduce the number of elements retrieved from the DB, this
patch, before processing the VLAN allocations per physical network,
deleted those registers belonging to any unconfigured physical network.

The VLAN registers per physical network are deleted using a bulk delete
operation, to speed up the process.

Those missing VLAN registers per network are now created using a bulk
insert operation, available in the ORM. This bulk operation speeds up
the sync process.

Change-Id: I8568e2277e157754aaff87a059a40e34e6a43e2b
Partial-Bug: #1862178
(cherry picked from commit 016e7826f165e69c3956375fc3aa8b8d642c9dc9)
(cherry picked from commit 651eb12bec5e5e986bed79f3a5c006c617e79bda)

commit_message:
Bump default tox env from py37 to py38

Python 3.8 is now our highest level supported python runtime.
This updates the default tox target environments to swap out
py37 for py38 to make sure local development testing is
covering this version.

This does not impact zuul jobs in any way, nor prevent local
tests against py37. It just changes the default if none is
explicitly provided.

Change-Id: Id0107e9cdabbc1435c709641b93cb5c90cdf6907
Signed-off-by: Sean McGinnis <sean.mcginnis@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Cleanup py27 support

This repo is now testing only with Python 3, so let's make
a few cleanups:
- Remove obsolete sections from setup.cfg
- Update requirements, no need for python_version anymore
- Cleanup doc/source/conf.py to remove now obsolete content.
- Use newer openstackdocstheme and sphinx versions
- Update constraints URL

Change-Id: I71fad2f2287477ae570ae40a8705b035bbc6a38e

Removing my vote for now while I look into live migration transient vs persistent domain more.'}, {'account_id': 25113, 'date': '2018-10-25 02:45:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

> (1 comment)
 > 
 > Removing my vote for now while I look into live migration transient
 > vs persistent domain more.

Thanks Melanie for the reviews. :) 

In nova [1], we can see that migration_flags contain libvirt.VIR_MIGRATE_PERSIST_DEST,  which would
make libvirt persist domain once migration is successful, see [2]. So IMHO, live migration should be always persistent. 

Based on above conclusions, libvirt would shut the domain off once it's migrated, and the qemu logs on the source host tell us like this:
...
2018-10-25 02:29:06.474+0000: initiating migration
2018-10-25 02:29:06.888+0000: shutting down, reason=migrated
2018-10-25T02:29:06.890002Z qemu-kvm: terminating on signal 15 from pid 1415 (/usr/sbin/libvirtd)
...

While the domain is SHUTOFF, and nova tries to call `self._domain.jobStats()`, we'll get VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID, but in such case, we should pretend the migration job is still running. Try to get domain job stats/info for just one or three more times, if domain is gone, we will get NO_DOMAIN error, which surely means migration job is successful, but if domain is still there which may because the ``qemu-kvm`` process (not libvirtd daemon process) is killed accidentally by OOM or other reasons, the migration job definitely fails. That's what I thoughts and that's why this patch was proposed. 

I made a test again this morning, and got source compute logs like this (the debug info may be slightly different):
...

tion job is still running by returning job type libvirt.VIR_DOMAIN_JOB_UNBOUNDED. Retry 1 time(s) after hitting VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID error. get_job_info /usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/nova/virt/lib
virt/guest.py:799

Looks like we'll not report FAILED for migrations that actually completed. As many times as I tried, I find that maybe just retry once, all problems are gone for good. 

And yes, the job info and job stats functionality only uses for live migration monitor.

LGTM,

We have been affected by this bug, and after few tests we  backported it our release to prevent disk loss.

About retry loop, I think it is necessary to avoid race condition.

To sumup what I understand:
 *We consider the successfull completion of live-migration in two case:
       - We were able to get end of jobs directly from libvirt because jobs was done and  by chance the domain was still up(not for long)
       - or we got VIR_ERR_NO_DOMAIN because we query jobs status on a domain already undefined by libvirt during its normal handover to dest host.
  *We should never consider instance SHUTOFF as a sucessfull live-migration, because it means that qemu have been killed out of scope of live migration process -> we have to abort 
  
But Because during the normal handover of livemigration libvirt shut instance just before undefined it, there is a gap of time where we can get an VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID (instance is shutoff)
  even for a successfull live-migration.

  So, retry mechanism here is necessary to me to distinguish:
         -instance shutoff by libvirt on the way to successfully finsh live migrastion
         -from qemu accidently got killed -> and we should abort.

To illustrate that: On a source host where instance-000081b2 is under live-migration:
while true ; do  echo XXXX; virsh domjobinfo instance-000081b2 ; sleep 0.2 ; done
....
XXXX
Job type:         Completed 
XXXX
error: Requested operation is not valid: domain is not running
XXXX
error: failed to get domain 'instance-000081b2'
error: Domain not found: no domain with matching name 'instance-000081b2'

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-10-22 07:51:46.000000000', 'message': "Retry after hitting libvirt error VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID in live migration.

When migration of a persistent guest completes, the guest merely shuts off,
but libvirt unhelpfully raises an VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID error code, in the
nova code, we pretend this case means success. But if we are in the middle of a
live migration, and sadly qemu-kvm process is killed accidentally,
such as by host OOM, which happens rarely in our environment but it does happen few
times, domain state is SHUTOFF and then we will get VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID
while trying to call `self._domain.jobStats()`. Under the circumstance,
migration should be considered failed, otherwise post_live_migration() function
starts to clean up instance files and we will lose customers' data forever.

In this patch, we `pretend` the migration job is still running after
hitting VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID and retry to get job stats for a few times,
which the count of retries can be configured. Because if migration succeeds
finally, we won't get VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID after some retries,
but the error code still happens if qemu-kvm process is killed accidentally.

Change-Id: I94aeda2156cd95e87b62da28e8b16cf7c1950a14
Closes-bug: #1799152
Signed-off-by: Fan Zhang <zh.f@outlook.com>
"}, {'created': '2018-10-23 02:47:59.000000000', 'message': 'Retry after hitting libvirt error VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID in live migration.

To avoid rare condition such as while live migration job is still
running, qemu-kvm is killed accidentally, and nova thinks the job
is done, then post live migration starts to clean instance files,
this patch proposes such changes:

1.Do not treat VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID as migration job completed.
2.`Pretend` the migration job is still running after hitting
  VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID by returning VIR_DOMAIN_JOB_UNBOUNDED for
  a few times.
3.Number of retries can be configured by CONF.job_info_retry_count.

Change-Id: I94aeda2156cd95e87b62da28e8b16cf7c1950a14
Closes-bug: #1799152

commit_message:
Retry after hitting libvirt error VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID in live migration.

To avoid rare condition such as while live migration job is still
running, qemu-kvm is killed accidentally, and nova thinks the job
is done, then post live migration starts to clean instance files,
this patch proposes such changes:

1.Do not treat VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID as migration job completed.
2.`Pretend` the migration job is still running after hitting
  VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID by returning VIR_DOMAIN_JOB_UNBOUNDED for
  a few times.
3.Number of retries can be configured by CONF.job_info_retry_count.

Change-Id: I94aeda2156cd95e87b62da28e8b16cf7c1950a14
Closes-bug: #1799152
Signed-off-by: Fan Zhang <zh.f@outlook.com>

commit_message:
CI: fix kayobe-tox-molecule job

The kayobe-tox-molecule job is currently failing on stable/train and
earlier branches. This was caused by the 13.0 release of the 'sh'
package [1]. A 13.1 release fixed this for Python 3, but there is no fix
available for Python 2 currently.

This change works around the issue by pinning 'sh' to <13.0 in
test-requirements.txt.

[1] https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/issues/2676

Change-Id: I0df1dadb3b48736cdbd25112517e524533550210
(cherry picked from commit 5f836518cfe964d2733f5a7db327fbfad3b8e8b0)

commit_message:
CI: fix kayobe-tox-molecule job

The kayobe-tox-molecule job is currently failing on stable/train and
earlier branches. This was caused by the 13.0 release of the 'sh'
package [1]. A 13.1 release fixed this for Python 3, but there is no fix
available for Python 2 currently.

This change works around the issue by pinning 'sh' to <13.0 in
test-requirements.txt.

[1] https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/issues/2676

Change-Id: I0df1dadb3b48736cdbd25112517e524533550210
(cherry picked from commit 5f836518cfe964d2733f5a7db327fbfad3b8e8b0)

cycle.

little more time. If so, update this path with the new commit

23 deadline.

commit_message:
Add "--labels-override" boolean option when creating a cluster

If "--label-override" is present, labels passwd with "cluster-create"
will be used, rather than labels retrieved from template, just like
current behaviour. If "--label-override" isn't present, labels retrieved
from template will be updated, if a label doesn't exit in template,
it will be added into labels passed to create cluster

Change-Id: Icbbd980148a33082339c51842c62b067132fce65
Task: 22202

subject: Allow overriding template labels on create
messages:
[{'account_id': 9995, 'date': '2018-12-03 15:48:57.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 9995, 'date': '2018-12-05 11:07:45.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 9995, 'date': '2018-12-05 15:52:17.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 6484, 'date': '2018-12-06 01:41:21.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 9995, 'date': '2018-12-06 09:24:40.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Thanks Feilong. Also not too happy, the code gets weird with this.

There seem to be a few cases when passing labels on cluster create:
1. we want to replace all cluster template labels with this new set
2. we want to override some labels, and keep the cluster template values for others
3. we want to drop some labels from the cluster template set

Would this work?

cluster-template labels: labelx=valuex,labely=valuey

1. --labels label_policy=replace,label1=value1,label2=value2 -> label1=value1,label2=value2
2. --labels label_policy=merge,labelx=valuexyz,label1=value1 -> labelx=valuexyz,labely=valuey,label1=value1
3. --labels label_policy,labelx= -> labelx=,labely=valuey

There's a corner case between not providing a label at all, and providing an empty value - wsme seems to have the Unset type for this case. If we want to follow this, we could add a '-' as a suffix to the label name to explicitly say the label should be dropped from the list. kubectl label works like this.

The 'label_policy' works and i think i'm ok with it, though it's not perfect."}, {'account_id': 9995, 'date': '2019-01-23 11:56:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

@feilong wang do you have any comments on the above?'}, {'account_id': 6484, 'date': '2019-01-24 01:52:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Sorry for the late response. This patch is slightly out of my attention after the Xmas holiday.

As for the case you mentioned "There's a corner case between not providing a label at all, and providing an empty value - wsme seems to have the Unset type for this case. If we want to follow this, we could add a '-' as a suffix to the label name to explicitly say the label should be dropped from the list. kubectl label works like this." If user is providing an empty value for --labels when create cluster, technically that doesn't mean the labels is being removed, it's just mean the label is going to be used with its default value. This can be work around by provide labels with the default value built-in current Magnum version.

If we don't like the new label_policy, then I would suggest using + instead of ++ and -.

Then +L1 means the L1 label in template will be replaced.
-L1 means the L1 label in template will be removed/replaced with default value.
L1 means adding new label not existing in the template.

If user passing in L1 and L1 existing in template, user get warning with 409.'}, {'account_id': 9995, 'date': '2019-04-10 21:39:07.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

> If user passing in L1 and L1 existing in template, user get warning
 > with 409.

I think this wouldn't be backwards compatible - end users have to pass the full set today to override one value, and your suggestion would break that if we start giving 409. They would get a message stating the issue, but for scripted deployments they would break.

I'll try to push something slightly different and see how it goes."}, {'account_id': 6484, 'date': '2019-04-10 21:42:31.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

That's a good point, re the script using. I'm keen to push this in, please keep going. Thanks."}, {'account_id': 9995, 'date': '2019-04-10 21:43:53.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Maybe the easiest is to add a new --labels-override and keep the --labels behavior, i can't come up with anything clean and backwards compatible."}, {'account_id': 20498, 'date': '2019-04-17 08:04:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Shall we pick this again?'}, {'account_id': 6484, 'date': '2019-08-26 21:57:10.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

@Ricardo, are you still working on this? This is really an annoying issue from end user view, let's get it done."}, {'account_id': 20498, 'date': '2019-08-27 17:54:16.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

https://review.opendev.org/#/c/657435/'}, {'account_id': 9995, 'date': '2019-08-27 21:03:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

> https://review.opendev.org/#/c/657435/

Why is there another patch for the same thing?'}, {'account_id': 9995, 'date': '2019-08-27 21:04:42.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

> @Ricardo, are you still working on this? This is really an annoying
 > issue from end user view, let's get it done.

Yes. I was waiting for some feedback... we know since long how annoying this is, thus the patch that has been waiting for a long time."}, {'account_id': 6484, 'date': '2019-09-11 01:59:20.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Hi Ricardo, I'm reviewing this patch again. And I'm wondering why we prefer to raise an error for case like:

openstack coe cluster create --labels ++label1=value111,label2=value2

What's the drawback if we support the mix case? Thanks."}, {'account_id': 9995, 'date': '2019-10-07 10:08:51.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

We're considering dropping this patch.

Instead the goal would be to distinguish between template labels and user specified labels at cluster creation. This will help with upgrades as well.

What is also needed:
* each driver needs to expose the labels it supports, and info describing if the label is updateable at cluster creation or node
* add a new field in the cluster table storing the cluster labels passed by the user

The drivers should then build the labels out of template labels + cluster labels, and should also validate the cluster labels passed by the client (both the keys and if they're updateable at creation).

The labels field in the cluster table could be deprecated, if it has any value it means the old behavior should be followed instead.

Spyros and Theodoros will follow this up elsewhere if it is agreed."}, {'account_id': 6484, 'date': '2019-10-07 20:48:53.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

If the scope of this patch is changing, then please submit a spec first since it's getting complicated.

I just reviewed https://review.opendev.org/#/c/657435/2/magnumclient/osc/v1/clusters.py and I like the idea of doing merge but instead of doing it on client side, I prefer to do the merging on server/api side.

You mentioned below 3 scenarios:

There seem to be a few cases when passing labels on cluster create:
1. we want to replace all cluster template labels with this new set
2. we want to override some labels, and keep the cluster template values for others
3. we want to drop some labels from the cluster template set


For a simple merging, it can easily satisfied the #1 and #2 cases. As for #3, I'm wondering do we really need it. Or can we really do it? Because all Magnum labels map to a heat param, and there must be a value for the param anyway. So when we say drop a label, how can we really drop it?

FWIW, let's start from spec for this issue and discuss more details there. Thank you for working on this."}, {'account_id': 28022, 'date': '2020-02-25 18:04:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

I'd like to revive this in some way as I expected "merge" to be the default behaviour but looks like all labels from cluster template get discarded which is a bit silly... defeats the point of having a cluster template in the first place. I'd like to see a merge behaviour by default going forward and with an option to replace. Also like the suggestion of a "-" suffix to delete exisiting labels from the cluster template.'}, {'account_id': 6484, 'date': '2020-03-08 20:52:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

@Spyros, @Ricardo, did you get a chance to discuss this? Any updates? Thanks.'}, {'account_id': 29425, 'date': '2020-03-26 09:42:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

im going to take this. 
I intend to give post a proposition next week'}, {'account_id': 28022, 'date': '2020-03-26 09:44:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

@dioguerra great news! look forward to it :)'}, {'account_id': 9995, 'date': '2020-04-02 13:19:59.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Should we abandon this in favor of https://review.opendev.org/#/c/716571?'}, {'account_id': 20498, 'date': '2020-04-29 11:53:39.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

yeap, thanks'}]

[{'created': '2018-12-03 15:48:57.000000000', 'message': "Allow overriding template labels on create

Allow overriding cluster template labels at cluster creation time. This
is done using a prefix '++' on the label name. As an example for
override:
openstack coe cluster template create ... \
    --labels label1=value1,label2=value2
openstack coe cluster create ... \
    --labels ++label1=value111,++label3=value3

In this example we override an existing value (label1), add a new label
not on the original template list (label3) and take the value of the
original template label (label2).

The previous behavior where no prefix '++' is given for any of the
labels is kept, with cluster labels taking over all labels from the
template.

One assumption is that if one value is overriden, then all values not
overriden are taken from the template. We could trigger an error if
necessary for something like:
openstack coe cluster create --labels ++label1=value111,label2=value2
( not no prefix ++ on label2 )

or simply document this behavior.

Change-Id: I933942372c69614b8c80eee6f56444f1d6152a98
Task: 22202
Story: 2002591

commit_message:
Allow overriding template labels on create

Allow overriding cluster template labels at cluster creation time. This
is done using a prefix '++' on the label name. As an example for
override:
openstack coe cluster template create ... \
    --labels label1=value1,label2=value2
openstack coe cluster create ... \
    --labels ++label1=value111,++label3=value3

In this example we override an existing value (label1), add a new label
not on the original template list (label3) and take the value of the
original template label (label2).

The previous behavior where no prefix '++' is given for any of the
labels is kept, with cluster labels taking over all labels from the
template.

One assumption is that if one value is overriden, then all values not
overriden are taken from the template. We could trigger an error if
necessary for something like:
openstack coe cluster create --labels ++label1=value111,label2=value2
( not no prefix ++ on label2 )

or simply document this behavior.

Change-Id: I933942372c69614b8c80eee6f56444f1d6152a98
Task: 22202
Story: 2002591

Add NodeGroup CLI specification

This is one of the specs divided from the orginal NodeGroup spec.
This spec will cover the new CLI APIs and changes to existing APIs
to support the NodeGroup features.

revisions:
[{'created': '2019-11-20 18:38:45.000000000', 'message': "Remove six and python 2.7 full support

Six is in use to help us to keep support for python 2.7.
Since the ussuri cycle we decide to remove the python 2.7
support so we can go ahead and also remove six usage from
the python code.

Review process and help
-----------------------
Removing six introduce a lot of changes and an huge amount of modified files
To simplify reviews we decided to split changes into several patches to avoid
painful reviews and avoid mistakes.

To review this patch you can use the six documentation [1] to obtain help and
understand choices.

Additional informations
-----------------------
Changes related to 'six.b(data)' [2]
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

six.b [2] encode the given datas in latin-1 in python3 so I did the same
things in this patch.

Latin-1 is equal to iso-8859-1 [3].

This encoding is the default encoding [4] of certain descriptive HTTP
headers.

I suggest to keep latin-1 for the moment and to move to another encoding
in a follow-up patch if needed to move to most powerful encoding (utf8).

HTML4 support utf8 charset and utf8 is the default charset for HTML5 [5].

Note that this commit message is autogenerated and not necesserly contains
changes related to 'six.b'

[1] https://six.readthedocs.io/
[2] https://six.readthedocs.io/#six.b
[3] https://docs.python.org/3/library/codecs.html#standard-encodings
[4] https://www.w3schools.com/charsets/ref_html_8859.asp
[5] https://www.w3schools.com/html/html_charset.asp

Patch 13 of a serie of 28 patches

Change-Id: I09aa3b7ddd93087c3f92c76c893c609cb9473842

commit_message:
Remove six and python 2.7 full support

Six is in use to help us to keep support for python 2.7.
Since the ussuri cycle we decide to remove the python 2.7
support so we can go ahead and also remove six usage from
the python code.

Review process and help
-----------------------
Removing six introduce a lot of changes and an huge amount of modified files
To simplify reviews we decided to split changes into several patches to avoid
painful reviews and avoid mistakes.

To review this patch you can use the six documentation [1] to obtain help and
understand choices.

Additional informations
-----------------------
Changes related to 'six.b(data)' [2]
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

six.b [2] encode the given datas in latin-1 in python3 so I did the same
things in this patch.

Latin-1 is equal to iso-8859-1 [3].

This encoding is the default encoding [4] of certain descriptive HTTP
headers.

I suggest to keep latin-1 for the moment and to move to another encoding
in a follow-up patch if needed to move to most powerful encoding (utf8).

HTML4 support utf8 charset and utf8 is the default charset for HTML5 [5].

Note that this commit message is autogenerated and not necesserly contains
changes related to 'six.b'

[1] https://six.readthedocs.io/

commit_message:
Install rabbitmq for ubuntu from external_repo

While S->T upgrade erlang being upgraded from 20.3 to 22.1 which
requires at least rabbitmq 3.8.0 while we have 3.7.8. So system installs
rabbitmq from distro packages to meet requirements, which eventually
apeears a more modern rabbitmq than we want.
So we pinn package version and install it from external source rather
from file,
as at the erlang upgrade stage repo is already configured and pinned.

Patch also disables upgrade jobs as they still don't catch relevant
commit.

Change-Id: I89019eb91b91b4f868361d575b781616f262171f

[{'created': '2020-04-16 17:42:55.000000000', 'message': "[doc] tell to prefix ipv6 hosts with inet6

Some environments with ipv6 used to connect with memcached servers
faced issues by omitting to prefix the host with the address family to
use.

Indeed libraries like python-memcached waiting for a prefix to
initialize the socket with the right address family. If the prefix
isn't given and that the host refer or bind an ipv6 then the socket
is initialized with an address family which correspond to an IPv4
and the connection doesn't work properly.

Openstack's puppet libraries already fixed that by introducing new
feature to automatically prefix the address if needed [1][2].

Anyway it could be worth to add more documentation on oslo.cache
to give more information to customers and avoid similar issues. These
changes aim to provide this documentation.

[1] https://review.opendev.org/#/q/status:merged+branch:master+topic:memcached-inet6-prefix

commit_message:
[doc] tell to prefix ipv6 hosts with inet6

Some environments with ipv6 used to connect with memcached servers
faced issues by omitting to prefix the host with the address family to
use.

Indeed libraries like python-memcached waiting for a prefix to
initialize the socket with the right address family. If the prefix
isn't given and that the host refer or bind an ipv6 then the socket
is initialized with an address family which correspond to an IPv4
and the connection doesn't work properly.

Openstack's puppet libraries already fixed that by introducing new
feature to automatically prefix the address if needed [1][2].

Anyway it could be worth to add more documentation on oslo.cache
to give more information to customers and avoid similar issues. These
changes aim to provide this documentation.

[1] https://review.opendev.org/#/q/status:merged+branch:master+topic:memcached-inet6-prefix
[2] https://review.opendev.org/#/c/661136/

Change-Id: I5e0b4818300348efe4625500792d9161281ed45a

commit_message:
Stop configuring install_command in tox.

Currently, we are overriding 'install_command' to use 'pip'. This is
considered poor behavior and 'python -m pip' should be used instead:

https://snarky.ca/why-you-should-use-python-m-pip/

It turns out that this is the the default value provided by tox:

https://tox.readthedocs.io/en/latest/config.html#conf-install_command

So we can remove the line and simply use the default value.

openstack-discuss thread
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-discuss/2020-April/014237.html

Bumping l-c:
-openstacksdk to 0.13.0
-Werkzeug to 0.14

Bumping t-r:
-openstacksdk to 0.13.0

Change-Id: I6e7e3792f2cede28ea9098ba546f415cec0ddf9b

commit_message:
[k8s] Fix no IP address in api_address

This is a corner case that when floating_ip_enabled=False,
master_lb_enabled=True,master_lb_floating_ip_enabled=False in
cluster template, but setting floating_ip_enabled=True when
creating the cluster. The current logic is not correct which
resulted in missing IP address in the api_address of cluster.

Task: 39519
Story: 2007586

Change-Id: I5e2ca270c4f4e2c48d067cd5b8f6609c037cb6e5
(cherry picked from commit 5dfb0d94c026a64c774b8363790002cdc15684fc)

commit_message:
Bump default tox env from py37 to py38

Python 3.8 is now our highest level supported python runtime.
This updates the default tox target environments to swap out
py37 for py38 to make sure local development testing is
covering this version.

This does not impact zuul jobs in any way, nor prevent local
tests against py37. It just changes the default if none is
explicitly provided.

Change-Id: I0bd1180719e4e093a24bc53424052354ad1cd900
Signed-off-by: Sean McGinnis <sean.mcginnis@gmail.com>

Add Python3 victoria unit tests

This is an automatically generated patch to ensure unit testing

Use unittest.mock instead of third party mock

Now that we no longer support py27, we can use the standard library
unittest.mock module instead of the third party mock lib.

commit_message:
[stable only] Remove timeout in config-download-export

With large number of nodes this can run for more than the
default timeout of 360s as we do fetch the whole config
from heat and generate the playbooks and the workflow can
timeout very easily.

This was removed for config-download worflow with
https://review.opendev.org/620627

Related-Bug: #1805649
Change-Id: Ib413a40a63c9d79e7387f854167d80a105888337

revisions:
[{'created': '2020-04-29 05:58:22.000000000', 'message': 'Use in-repo GPG keys

We make remote network hits to get the GPG keys which are quite
unreliable and causes numerous CI failures so this change installs
them from files inside the role.

The implementation here is derived from that which was done in the
galera_server role in I7ac1a5e3a05aa3d0b4fae86c4a325ef147a9a528.

Change-Id: I6d0f11709a1c2ff38a43d4a29565fe63be4a9879
'}]
commit_message:
Use in-repo GPG keys

We make remote network hits to get the GPG keys which are quite
unreliable and causes numerous CI failures so this change installs
them from files inside the role.

The implementation here is derived from that which was done in the
galera_server role in I7ac1a5e3a05aa3d0b4fae86c4a325ef147a9a528.

Change-Id: I6d0f11709a1c2ff38a43d4a29565fe63be4a9879

commit_message:
Ensure that external network don't have any ports before deletion

In module
neutron_tempest_plugin.api.admin.test_external_network_extension
we need to ensure that there is no any leftover ports, like e.g.
floatingip_agent_gateway port before network deletion.

Closes-bug: #1875344

Change-Id: I8226e999d9ec8e521b39ab915aaa503425174987

commit_message:
Remove deprecated nova::metadata::enable_proxy_headers_parsing

The nova::metadata::enable_proxy_headers_parsing parameter was
deprecated in puppet-nova[1], and is useless now because we set
nova::api::enable_proxy_headers_parsing already.

[1] 7c1717af69d2659703833e9fefe9af86664d2e29

commit_message:
[ci] Use magnum-tempest-plugin-tests-api

This commit drops magnum-functional-api (which uses legacy-dsvm-base due
to be removed in the V cycle) in favour of
magnum-tempest-plugin-tests-api defined in the magnum-tempest-plugins
repo (which uses the new devstack-tempest job recommended for running
Tempest tests in Zuul v3) for API Tempest tests.

Story: 2007561
Task: 39443

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/#/c/721077/

Change-Id: I91446f8773ecec1286c9913c3fff688bd8d9a087

commit_message:
[Q->T] Alow supplying command options to leapp

Leapp now allows providing custom repos for upgrade. To use this one
has to provide "--enablerepo <reponame 1> --enablerepo <reponame 2>".

Change-Id: I23696700688042408005b2a6556a854ec523e8d7

commit_message:
Enable focal and ussuri for the charm

The charm requires a bundle force override for the focal bundle.  This
patch adds test bundles for bionic-ussuri and focal-ussuri to the charm.

Change-Id: I6e6cbb30fe7b525a49b7c79181b5aaeb2e129cca

commit_message:
Improve test coverage

Added a number of unit tests based on coverage report
data, it's up to 79% now.

Fixed test_pool_create_exception() to call pool_create()
instead of pool_update().

Also fixed a bug in the driver.pool_update() exception code
path found when adding a new test, status['pools'] is the
correct element.

Change-Id: Ic72aad21e0ecf5b0334b321b18515d909daa3ba4
(cherry picked from commit eb1e24ac46f458887a31ffde54342ec2e34345f7)

> any clues? @Marcin @ironic-cores (Dmitry, Iury and others :-) )

First of all - do not assume that 1st partition is EFI System Partition. It does not have to be first - it just need to have proper partition type (0xFE00). In CirrOS image it is partition number 15th.

Second thing: do not assume that there are files on rootfs partition. They may be but do not have to be there. CirrOS copies contents of it's initramfs to / on first boot.

Those two are common things people have issues with. If that info does not help then tomorrow I can take a look at your code."}, {'account_id': 10239, 'date': '2020-03-18 08:01:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

I'm trying to make the job less resource-greedy: https://review.opendev.org/#/c/713586/

commit_message:
Update TOX/UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/ussuri

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

Until the requirements repository has as stable/ussuri branch, tests will
continue to use the upper-constraints list on master.

Change-Id: I20344db2a6d89fdc4e97a3dc03a76bff61a41b14

Use unittest.mock instead of third party mock

Now that we no longer support py27, we can use the standard library
unittest.mock module instead of the third party mock lib.

Signed-off-by: Sean McGinnis <sean.mcginnis@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Replace six.iteritems() with .items()

1.As mentioned in [1], we should avoid using
six.iteritems to achieve iterators.
We can use dict.items instead, as it will return
iterators in PY3 as well. And dict.items/keys will more readable.
2.In py2, the performance about list should be negligible, see the link [2].
[1] https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Python3
[2] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-June/066391.html

Change-Id: I9cf36db9e18d02238ebbfa6962f0ac76d694a43a

correctly endpoints like: 'https://<ip>:<port>/v1',
'https://<ip>:<port>/swift/v1'.

commit_message:
Update TOX/UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/ussuri

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

Until the requirements repository has as stable/ussuri branch, tests will
continue to use the upper-constraints list on master.

Change-Id: Iadf66b784540b8ee7393841792a11fe6e3416cfa

commit_message:
Move unit tests execution to stestr

From time to time, unit tests execution fails with error: "TypeError:
'NoneType' object is not iterable". It seems that problem is in
unittest2 library, which is used by testtools for executing the tests.
Stestr lib is usinig unittest by default and the problem does not appear
for several hundred launches.

Authored-By: danpawlik <dpawlik@redhat.com>

Change-Id: I6646629128d9265b5fb7390dc131c55cf34a07ca
Signed-off-by: Gael Chamoulaud (Strider) <gchamoul@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Re-validate healthcheck work on nova/keystone containers

They were disabled until the native podman healthcheck was integrated in
tripleo-ansible and it finally merged; so we can remove that safeguard
and it should be working.

commit_message:
Set Neutron's l3_ha flag to True in standalone ML2/OVS job

Even if this is standalone job, when l3_ha config option is set
to True in Neutron server, all routers will be created as HA
routers.
So for each such router created during the tests things like
keepalived, neutron-keepalived-state-change-monitor will be spawned
and also HA network will be created for tenants used by Tempest.
This will give us better coverage of things which are most commonly
used in Neutron.

Change-Id: I44ed60e88723e58ff1bb7bd0559540a596442f5a
(cherry picked from commit c53f747b1a96e696a44d6962e7624f49640e6a61)

Currently, we are overriding 'install_command' to use 'pip'. This is
considered poor behavior and 'python -m pip' should be used instead:

https://snarky.ca/why-you-should-use-python-m-pip/

It turns out that this is the the default value provided by tox:

https://tox.readthedocs.io/en/latest/config.html#conf-install_command

So we can remove the line and simply use the default value.

openstack-discuss thread

Stop configuring install_command in tox.

Currently, we are overriding 'install_command' to use 'pip'. This is
considered poor behavior and 'python -m pip' should be used instead:

https://snarky.ca/why-you-should-use-python-m-pip/

It turns out that this is the the default value provided by tox:

https://tox.readthedocs.io/en/latest/config.html#conf-install_command

So we can remove the line and simply use the default value.

openstack-discuss thread
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-discuss/2020-April/014237.html

Bumping pbr since oslo.log requires 3.1.1

Change-Id: I1f968c724e79e04bbc2fe8cb26fd54404b0350e0

commit_message:
Upgrade centos in dockerfiles

Somehow an update to centos repos and the fact that docker.io centos
containers weren't updated for a while broke us. To fix this we need to
make sure RPMs in the container are upgraded, otherwise `yum history
undo last` fails miserably with missing packages errors.

Also this commit makes sure installation dies when we're unable to build
containers.

Change-Id: I29e19e13aa22047bfa07817a7794fc18612bbc32

commit_message:
[ussuri][goal] Drop python 2.7 support and testing

OpenStack is dropping the py2.7 support in ussuri cycle.

This also adds the standard expected jobs to be run for ussuri.

Complete discussion & schedule can be found in
- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-discuss/2019-October/010142.html
- https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/drop-python2-support

Ussuri Communtiy-wide goal:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/selected/ussuri/drop-py27.html

Various fixes to make the expected jobs pass as well.

Change-Id: I3e8c107c9e3cb8a13a531fb81fd2030d0aad0e7e
Signed-off-by: Sean McGinnis <sean.mcginnis@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Update verbosity so it is consistently set

This change will set the verbosity consistently whenever a playbook is
executed via the client.

All tests have been updated to ensure that the verbosity setting is always
defined when a playbook is executed.

Change-Id: I35b10d48344c8b7f71186bc529a300f75d7b8d63
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kecarter@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Add login flag to container image prepare defaults

If a registry requires authentication and --local-push-destination is
not used, a user may need to enable the login functionality. This change
adds a --enable-registry-login flag to `openstack container image
prepare default` that can be used to ensure the
ContainerImageRegistryLogin flag is defined as true.  Previously this
would have needed to be added in elsewhere.

Change-Id: I809023604fe119ba162638d921ffec56d4eb72f2
(cherry picked from commit c08c5c2b9299f47a0f1c8103b5ccafae1cf2b766)

commit_message:
Avoid raising NetworkInterfaceNotFound exception in DHCP agent logs

In "ip_lib.ensure_device_is_ready", before retrieving the interface
attributes, a check is done to know if the interface exists. In case
it does not exist, the exception "NetworkInterfaceNotFound" will not
be raised and written in the logs.

Conflicts:
    neutron/privileged/agent/linux/ip_lib.py

commit_message:
Forwards LOGOUT_URL to templates.

Uses the openstack context preprocessor to pass
the LOGOUT_URL from settings to templates and
changes the 'Sign out' menu entry to redirect to it
instead of the logout view directly.

closes-bug: #1747149
Change-Id: Id17ffca6b5e24779433c3f19d009bb2a77f7b901
(cherry picked from commit a11aa7ff62c15d7bf15367106f933ef0ae5d4521)

commit_message:
Move /etc/ssh/ssh_known_hosts bind mount where it's needed

There is no need to bind mount /etc/ssh/ssh_known_hosts for all the
containers. It's only useful for nova_compute and nova_libvirt
containers where live migration needs that file to work.

Change-Id: I9765dedf43d2c6765922eafaa9d5791ce488b41f
(cherry picked from commit d1bf6c6f21a1267171450feee4178e90b104cae3)

commit_message:
Improve VLAN allocations synchronization

In order to reduce the number of elements retrieved from the DB, this
patch, before processing the VLAN allocations per physical network,
deleted those registers belonging to any unconfigured physical network.

The VLAN registers per physical network are deleted using a bulk delete
operation, to speed up the process.

Those missing VLAN registers per network are now created using a bulk
insert operation, available in the ORM. This bulk operation speeds up
the sync process.

Conflicts:
      neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/type_vlan.py

Change-Id: I8568e2277e157754aaff87a059a40e34e6a43e2b
Partial-Bug: #1862178
(cherry picked from commit 016e7826f165e69c3956375fc3aa8b8d642c9dc9)
(cherry picked from commit 651eb12bec5e5e986bed79f3a5c006c617e79bda)
(cherry picked from commit 4fff732b76ee5d9a4917901b33ce80ccafb5203f)
(cherry picked from commit 8a6521e4457acbd7ceed941f363ee7c9872422ba)

commit_message:
Remove healthcheck from ceilometer_gnocchi_upgrade container

Not sure why ceilometer_gnocchi_upgrade has healthcheck key in its
configuration but the container isn't managed by systemd and it's only
running a one-off shell command to upgrade ceilometer so it should not
have a healthcheck.

Change-Id: I38aa38099a2d759c1b1f2e14d64c36d52c0b1c0e
Related-Bug: #1873249
(cherry picked from commit d78ce138f67aee2f2bf9c5d0db89a5b1e4b16fb0)

commit_message:
Make sure octavia uses internal endpoint to barbican

The octavia service communicates to the barbican service with
public endpoint_type by default[1], it should use internal
like other services.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/octavia/blob/0056b5175f89070164849501ec6d960549b95e34/octavia/common/config.py#L533-L537

Closes-Bug: #1875618
Change-Id: I90d2b0aeac090a3e2366341e260232fc1f0d6492

commit_message:
Don't use neutron dns search domain

If there is a neutron search domain available don't use
it since we use the Juju provider dns for the o-hm0 port.

Change-Id: I369d7708f7149e7b491c0f4a1f86126cb0707373
Related-Bug: #1845303

commit_message:
Update TOX_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/ussuri

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

Until the requirements repository has as stable/ussuri branch, tests will
continue to use the upper-constraints list on master.

Change-Id: Ic80bab080295a52753de2e11be585f3868878e8c

commit_message:
Update TOX_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/ussuri

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

Until the requirements repository has as stable/ussuri branch, tests will
continue to use the upper-constraints list on master.

Change-Id: I6353c96c9109fc0549fce8b033845e54c9dd28ee

commit_message:
[Unity] Support create volume with tiering policy.

four supported values:
  - ``StartHighThenAuto``(default)
  - ``Auto``
  - ``HighestAvailable``
  - ``LowestAvailable``

commit_message:
CI: Fix Debian aarch64 jobs

Debian defaults to Python2 which is not complete in aarch64 images.
This patch changes CI to always use Python3.

We need to install several Python modules to have working ussuri jobs.

"Failed to import the required Python library (setuptools) on primary's Python /usr/bin/python3."

And then several Python2 ones for train->ussuri upgrade jobs:

"Unable to find any of pip2 to use. pip needs to be installed."

Change-Id: Ia0d3ff15d97d1cabbb0b8e7f32e8712ca3f94732

commit_message:
Drop python 2.7 support and testing

Ussuri Communtiy-wide goal:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/selected/ussuri/drop-py27.html

Remove explicit listed jobs from check queue, they are in the templates.

- Update jobs
- Remove python 2.7 stanza from setup.py
- Add requires on python >= 3.6 to setup.cfg so that pypi and pip
  know about the requirement
- Remove obsolete sections from setup.cfg:
  * Wheel is not needed for python 3 only repo
  * Some other sections are obsolete
- Update classifiers
- Update requirements, no need for python_version anymore

Co-Authored-By: Andreas Jaeger <aj@suse.com>
Change-Id: I4a1976c78b0fe69cc1b423c516d557838cb6d59b

commit_message:
[stable-only] Raise error for temp_ssh_key import failure

We should not be ignoring the error as we would skip the
admin-enablement workflow and running ansible playbooks would
fail later.

Change-Id: I69c79b3bfec4467210ca6c480f61e14cbf1d0a44
Partial-Bug: #1873892

commit_message:
[Storwize] Add an option to specify iSCSI IP version

Spectrum Virtualize Family Cinder driver support bot IPv4 and IPv6
address for iSCSI Connection. In some scenario, especially test
environment, server has both IPv4 and IPv6 address configured, but User
want to select specific IP version for iSCSI connection. This patch
aim to resolve this kind of issue.

Co-Author: lixqin@cn.ibm.com

Change-Id: Ief8304ded53e8e10b366d698282bb976d65fdc59
Closes-Bug: #1855717

Update TOX_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/ussuri

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

Until the requirements repository has as stable/ussuri branch, tests will
continue to use the upper-constraints list on master.

commit_message:
Workaround in NetworkSegmentRange OVO until "project_id" migration

The "network_segment_range" service plugin API does not have
"tenant_id" as parameter. However, because the migration from
"tenant_id" to "project_id" did not finish, every OVO with
"project_id" will also have "tenant_id" as an extra field. This
extra field will be populated with the same value as the
"project_id" field.

If the Neutron API WSGI is used and "tenant_id" is not present in
the API (defined in neutron-lib), both "tenant_id" and "project_id"
parameters will be removed from the response.

This patch introduces a workaround for this OVO until the migration
is over.

More information about this patch can be found in the bug c#4.

Change-Id: I85a02d8b59e8a758826c110e00df84672fa93676
Closes-Bug: #1828205
(cherry picked from commit 3053caaa02adaadfffa53fb1070aaa60f49419e8)
(cherry picked from commit c945e5ccbadf35d1422828f654a960caf2cd979c)

commit_message:
Set a default IP route metric in ip_lib.list_ip_routes

By default, if no metric is defined, the kernel interprets the
highest value (0).

The current implementation, using pyroute2, is a translation from
the CLI command "ip route". This command uses the netlink API to
communicate with the kernel. In IPv6, when the metric value is not
set is translated as 1024 as default [1].

[1]https://access.redhat.com/solutions/3659171

Change-Id: I0c5f9e320bbbf314a2d6a22c515bf903de84cdaf
Related-Bug: #1855759
(cherry picked from commit 7593f95a741aec62d9956175ce6d3ce1b1abb9a0)

commit_message:
Update TOX_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/ussuri

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

Until the requirements repository has as stable/ussuri branch, tests will
continue to use the upper-constraints list on master.

Change-Id: Ie1009a0048c697f5290f9ea202fe144b4064edb0

commit_message:
Refactor ansible inventory generation

- Removes the incorrect swift_url lookup
- Removes the usage of session object
- Removes os_auth_token for undercloud
- Moves the code to inventory module for it to be used in ansible
module

commit_message:
Add login flag to container image prepare defaults

If a registry requires authentication and --local-push-destination is
not used, a user may need to enable the login functionality. This change
adds a --enable-registry-login flag to `openstack container image
prepare default` that can be used to ensure the
ContainerImageRegistryLogin flag is defined as true.  Previously this
would have needed to be added in elsewhere.

Change-Id: I809023604fe119ba162638d921ffec56d4eb72f2

[{'created': '2020-04-24 14:55:27.000000000', 'message': 'Split out selinux management

Currently if you have selinux enabled on the undercloud but disable it
for the overcloud, selinux is disabled on the undercloud during the
deployment. This can be resolved by only managing the selinux setting
for the deployment target hosts rather than the all.

Change-Id: I94b81ea0b954cdba7704720a145b752fa58d4308
Closes-Bug: #1874828
'}]
commit_message:
Split out selinux management

Currently if you have selinux enabled on the undercloud but disable it
for the overcloud, selinux is disabled on the undercloud during the
deployment. This can be resolved by only managing the selinux setting
for the deployment target hosts rather than the all.

Change-Id: I94b81ea0b954cdba7704720a145b752fa58d4308
Closes-Bug: #1874828

commit_message:
[ussuri][goal] drop python 2.7 support

OpenStack is dropping the py2.7 support in ussuri cycle except
swift and sorlets which is exception approved in this goal.

Somehow this repo is left to remove the support of py2.7.

Ussuri Communtiy-wide goal:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/selected/ussuri/drop-py27.html

Change-Id: I0b8a896ce64a4b31c11444a2af45ae503ad089f1

commit_message:
zuul: Switch to the Zuulv3 grenade job

This change switches the single node legacy grenade-py3 job over to the
newly introduced Zuulv3 based grenade job.

Change-Id: I212692905a1d645cd911c2a161c13c794c0e0f4d

commit_message:
Support for PowerMax Volume Config

PowerMax config options have changed since newton.
Updating them to the latest. Supports both iSCSI and FC
drivers.

Supports deploying multiple instances of the
cinder::backend::dellemc_powermax backend
(e.g. one iscsi + one fc, multiple iscsi, etc.).

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/#/c/708960/
Change-Id: I25be51121390afd7ed3d0f0249733d3ccaf557de

commit_message:
Focal enablement

Added support for charm to install py3 packages

Fixed gss script to run on both py2 and py3

Added the ability for the script wrapper to get the distro version
so the gss script can be launched with the right python binary.

focal-ussuri test bundle added and smoke/dev tests changed to focal-ussuri

charmhelpers sync

-----
LP related bug: #1853456

Change-Id: I161d8a0fa9787f0d5409f7bf386c22d98aae0a64

commit_message:
Cleanup py27 support

This repo is now testing only with Python
3, so let's make a few cleanups:
- Remove setup.* files, they are not needed
  for this repo
- Cleanup */source/conf.py to remove now
  obsolete content.
- Remove install_command, the default is fine;
  move constraints into deps

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/720558
Change-Id: Ic6ea57d750a203b5a8f199b78dd3c0889b849df9

commit_message:
[ussuri][goal] Updates for python 2.7 drop

OpenStack is dropping the py2.7 support in ussuri cycle.

Only update required is in tox to define common baspython as py3 os that
all tox env including [testenv:functional] will use py3 instead of py2.

Complete discussion & schedule can be found in
- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-discuss/2019-October/010142.html
- https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/drop-python2-support

Ussuri Communtiy-wide goal:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/selected/ussuri/drop-py27.html

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/720558
Change-Id: I4994a888c81ad414a95ea4186638ad27a8bb3c71

commit_message:
Remove redundant listen on haproxy handler

Follow-up on [1] "Avoid multiple haproxy restarts after
reconfiguration".

There is no need to duplicate handler name in listen.
The issue was because we had two handlers with the same
name in the same environment.
This causes Ansible not to mark handler as already run.

[1] https://review.opendev.org/708385

Change-Id: I5425a8037b6860ef71bce59becff8dfe5b601d4c
Related-Bug: #1864810
(cherry picked from commit 98e86ea62b64eb1c5a7dfaca6c366527f584afc0)

commit_message:
Cleanup py27 support

This repo is now testing only with Python 3, so let's make
a few cleanups:
- Remove python 2.7 stanza from setup.py
- Remove obsolete sections from setup.cfg
- Update classifiers
- Use newer openstackdocstheme and Sphinx versions
- Cleanup */source/conf.py to remove now obsolete content.
- Remove install_command from tox.ini, the default is fine
- Remove hacking requirements from lower-constraints, they
  are not needed for install

Change-Id: I150a5ee2cd08abf5ce9cf9daf2835007dea0dffd

commit_message:
Expose voting-only option for master-eligible elasticsearch nodes

Master-eligible Elasticsearch nodes can be prevented from winning
elections by enabling voting_only mode. This is particularly useful
where certain nodes need to be master-eligible for cluster
discovery and formation, but shouldn't be able to actually become
the master node for the entire cluster. This commit exposes the
option in the elasticsearch role to set this. The default behaviour
remains the same, with all master-eligible able to win elections.

Change-Id: Ieba965af57c86e3b3767444883114f0130d3f000

commit_message:
Add support for Consul ACL token parameter. Switch to python-consul2
library which is a fork of python-consul which is no longer maintained.

When running Consul with ACLs enabled, the best practice is to default deny
all. In order to support applying a policy to the tooz coordination KV store
path, passing through an ACL is needed.

Closes-Bug: #1752205
Change-Id: I98fc96468b21368ce66365e3fc38c495b1f2918a

consul

Change-Id: Iacf8c72e768ed01a6295eeab20220acd243eb2ad

more acl_tokens

Change-Id: Ib2d37834056eb522cd04572bf56f13ab33715c4c

Revert "update sys reqs"

This reverts commit 57d207f5

Change-Id: If5f758c0558326536e7c6a56342839ba90411dc2

Use unittest.mock instead of third party mock

Now that we no longer support py27, we can use the standard library
unittest.mock module instead of the third party mock lib.

Signed-off-by: Sean McGinnis <sean.mcginnis@gmail.com>

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

'}]
commit_message:
Update TOX_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/ussuri

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

Until the requirements repository has as stable/ussuri branch, tests will
continue to use the upper-constraints list on master.

Change-Id: I9bfc3a17b9b69e4a6206860132273f59ce93d5e2

commit_message:
Cleanup py27 support

This repo is now testing only with Python 3, so let's make
a few cleanups:
- Remove python 2.7 stanza from setup.py
- Remove obsolete sections from setup.cfg
- Remove install_command from tox.ini, the default is fine

Change-Id: I6639d4b8612f9f50c98da43aec24cc7dbdb87634

commit_message:
Use Zuulv3 devstack jobs

This patch updates the gate jobs to stop using legacy
jobs and use the new Zuul v3 jobs instead.

The tempest tests will be re-enabled in a future patch.

Train only.

The version of RabbitMQ shipped in the CentOS 7 rabbitmq image is
incompatible with that shipped in the CentOS 8 rabbitmq image. Kolla
provides a rabbitmq-3.7.24 image on CentOS 7 only, which can be used as
a path for migration from CentOS 7 ro CentOS 8.

This change adds a 'rabbitmq_use_3_7_24_on_centos7' flag which can be
set to 'true' to deploy rabbitmq-3.7.24 on CentOS 7. The image should be

Partially-Implements: blueprint centos-rhel-8
"}]
commit_message:
CentOS 8: add flag to deploy rabbitmq-3.7.24 on CentOS 7

Train only.

The version of RabbitMQ shipped in the CentOS 7 rabbitmq image is
incompatible with that shipped in the CentOS 8 rabbitmq image. Kolla
provides a rabbitmq-3.7.24 image on CentOS 7 only, which can be used as
a path for migration from CentOS 7 ro CentOS 8.

This change adds a 'rabbitmq_use_3_7_24_on_centos7' flag which can be
set to 'true' to deploy rabbitmq-3.7.24 on CentOS 7. The image should be
deployed via 'kolla-ansible upgrade'.

Change-Id: I73b131a32e7157965ad0248584cad53f0de03898
Partially-Implements: blueprint centos-rhel-8

commit_message:
Update TOX_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/ussuri

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

Until the requirements repository has as stable/ussuri branch, tests will
continue to use the upper-constraints list on master.

Change-Id: I2335edbe3f5fbc891d85bd56ce1ed62607b331ec

commit_message:
Update share-manager behavior for shrink share operation

This patch updates the share-manager to handle with the
"ShareShrinkingPossibleDataLoss" driver exception in an appropriate way
by setting the status to "available", and sending to the user an error
message warning that the shrink operation was not completed.

Change-Id: Ie1e7fcbf116d3fd831e550aa70f02a3aa60291b8
Related-Bug: #1858328
Depends-On: Idf34a149e5a975d5fbced0ec78d102c5d90b87c6

commit_message:
Cleanup py27 support

Make a few cleanups:
- Remove python 2.7 stanza from setup.py
- Add requires on python >= 3.6 to setup.cfg so that pypi and pip
  know about the requirement
- Remove obsolete sections from setup.cfg:
  * Wheel is not needed for python 3 only repo
  * Some other sections are obsolete
- Update classifiers
- Update requirements, no need for python_version anymore

Change-Id: I45b5b8582b67b39823a6e21221c491842b390b96

commit_message:
Use unittest.mock instead of third party mock

Now that we no longer support py27, we can use the standard library
unittest.mock module instead of the third party mock lib.

Change-Id: I8c57cd214c8f185eb9a894928278fa31c6a16222
Signed-off-by: Sean McGinnis <sean.mcginnis@gmail.com>

commit_message:
drop tripleo-common-tempest-plugin

This is not needed plugin without any branches or releases. And wants Python 3
while we have Py2 for CentOS 7.

Add support on extend_share to glusterfs driver

This patch adds extend_share support for the share glusterfs driver.

Change-Id: Ib187597c378448b85fce637f1a1d33560084bbe2
Signed-off-by: guojiannan <guojiannan@cmss.chinamobile.com>
Signed-off-by: chenfangxian <chenfangxian@cmss.chinamobile.com>

commit_message:
Remove translation sections from setup.cfg

These translation sections are not needed anymore, Babel can
generate translation files without them.

Remove babel.cfg as well, this is the default role and not needed
anymore.

Change-Id: I4d1665f1442b15c0efe3c9c8b04d0f5226902b0c

commit_message:
Add first unit test for race conditions

This is a POC to show how we can simulate race conditions in the unit
tests. It basically sets a breakpoint to the first DB interactions
and calls the former function again. This can be also used to simulate
more complex situations (like parallel create and delete action).

See also: http://www.oreills.co.uk/2015/03/01/testing-race-conditions-in-python.html

Partly-implements: bp eliminate-race-conditions

Change-Id: Ibf92b9d4f033d1cc01043c2f25a905f10f1d675b

Don't check server connection if it w/o IP addr

In case a server doesn't have an IP addr
(its status is error), don't check server connection.

commit_message:
Update master for stable/ussuri

Add file to the reno documentation build to show release notes for
stable/ussuri.

Use pbr instruction to increment the minor version number
automatically so that master versions are higher than the versions on
stable/ussuri.

Change-Id: I2cc36196855091e579a975fba40cb18681866959

Add undercloud-containers to gate

This patch adds a TripleO job to our gate to make sure
we don't break TripleO with API changes again.

commit_message:
Re-enable local hacking checks

With the switch to hacking 2.0, the local checks are not enabled
anymore, update repo to use the new way of registering local checks.

Remove local vi check since hacking has this now as H106.

Change-Id: I4d03f4c7eff959017e907cac974c394af0559643

commit_message:
Update README

The CloudKeep organization was removed from GitHub for unknown
reasons.  This patch removes any mention of a CloudKeep project
as they were all vaporware anyway.

Also fixed the python-barbicanclient to point to opendev.org as
it is the official repo, and the reop at github.com is a mirror.

Change-Id: If45f75b0c0e7bbab0c0a74fb9a027ad87068a7f1
